{"ts": 0.0, "op": "recall", "ids": ["mem_1242ebb5", "mem_fc0b496d", "mem_c827640c", "mem_f27a3d78", "mem_0635fdb6"], "query": "URLValidator invalid characters username password", "meta": {"k": 5, "n": 5, "hits": [{"id": "mem_1242ebb5", "content": "The URLValidator test suite loads URLs from tests/validators/valid_urls.txt (expected valid) and tests/validators/invalid_urls.txt (expected invalid) for dynamic test generation.", "score": 3.891045, "tokens": 44, "rank": 0, "timestamp": 1782446965.32824}, {"id": "mem_fc0b496d", "content": "The fix adds `if username is None or password is None: return` after the username extraction from kwargs on line 42-43 of django/contrib/auth/backends.py.", "score": 3.66291, "tokens": 38, "rank": 1, "timestamp": 1782450004.963297}, {"id": "mem_c827640c", "content": "The Django admin JSONField displays Unicode characters (e.g., Chinese) as ASCII escape sequences (\\uXXXX) because `json.dumps()` defaults to `ensure_ascii=True`.", "score": 2.089872, "tokens": 40, "rank": 2, "timestamp": 1782456518.445946}, {"id": "mem_f27a3d78", "content": "The bug: Django username validators (both ASCII and Unicode) accepted usernames ending with a newline because `$` in the original regex `r'^[\\w.@+-]+$'` matched before a trailing `\\n`.", "score": 1.960066, "tokens": 46, "rank": 3, "timestamp": 1782448126.416309}, {"id": "mem_0635fdb6", "content": "Valid URL test cases added to valid_urls.txt with percent-encoded special characters in auth: http://user%40name@example.com, http://user:[REDACTED:Basic Auth Credentials]@example.com, http://user%2Fname@example.com.", "score": 1.767903, "tokens": 54, "rank": 4, "timestamp": 1782446965.32824}]}}
{"ts": 0.0, "op": "recall", "ids": ["mem_fc0b496d", "mem_14017f5e", "mem_1242ebb5", "mem_02f5c361", "mem_f27a3d78", "mem_0635fdb6", "mem_82c35002", "mem_0e0f02ea", "mem_2c61e221", "mem_6ffcc2ea"], "query": "PR 10097 URLValidator username password test cases requirements", "meta": {"k": 10, "n": 10, "hits": [{"id": "mem_fc0b496d", "content": "The fix adds `if username is None or password is None: return` after the username extraction from kwargs on line 42-43 of django/contrib/auth/backends.py.", "score": 4.636481, "tokens": 38, "rank": 0, "timestamp": 1782450004.963297}, {"id": "mem_14017f5e", "content": "The bug was introduced in commit bbe6fbb8768e8fb1aecb96d51c049d7ceaf802d3 and addressed in PR #14315.", "score": 3.787284, "tokens": 25, "rank": 1, "timestamp": 1782458477.665685}, {"id": "mem_1242ebb5", "content": "The URLValidator test suite loads URLs from tests/validators/valid_urls.txt (expected valid) and tests/validators/invalid_urls.txt (expected invalid) for dynamic test generation.", "score": 3.347103, "tokens": 44, "rank": 2, "timestamp": 1782446965.32824}, {"id": "mem_02f5c361", "content": "The `test_negative` test in `tests/utils_tests/test_dateparse.py` covers negative duration cases: '-4 15:30', '-172800', '-15:30', '-1:15:30', and '-30.1'.", "score": 2.50459, "tokens": 38, "rank": 3, "timestamp": 1782447910.900201}, {"id": "mem_f27a3d78", "content": "The bug: Django username validators (both ASCII and Unicode) accepted usernames ending with a newline because `$` in the original regex `r'^[\\w.@+-]+$'` matched before a trailing `\\n`.", "score": 2.340195, "tokens": 46, "rank": 4, "timestamp": 1782448126.416309}, {"id": "mem_0635fdb6", "content": "Valid URL test cases added to valid_urls.txt with percent-encoded special characters in auth: http://user%40name@example.com, http://user:[REDACTED:Basic Auth Credentials]@example.com, http://user%2Fname@example.com.", "score": 2.067821, "tokens": 54, "rank": 5, "timestamp": 1782446965.32824}, {"id": "mem_82c35002", "content": "The test test_crash_password_does_not_leak in tests/dbshell/test_postgresql.py had the same `if env:` bug pattern, which was fixed to `if env is not None:`.", "score": 1.798161, "tokens": 39, "rank": 6, "timestamp": 1782458477.665685}, {"id": "mem_0e0f02ea", "content": "Tests for PostgreSQL dbshell SSL options are in tests/dbshell/test_postgresql.py and verify each SSL parameter (sslcert, sslkey, sslmode, sslrootcert) individually and all together with password.", "score": 1.648179, "tokens": 48, "rank": 7, "timestamp": 1782448949.899602}, {"id": "mem_2c61e221", "content": "In Django's MySQL backend `get_connection_params`, the deprecated kwargs `'db'` and `'passwd'` must be replaced with `'database'` and `'password'` respectively when connecting to mysqlclient.", "score": 1.39181, "tokens": 47, "rank": 8, "timestamp": 1782458768.24938}, {"id": "mem_6ffcc2ea", "content": "MySQL DatabaseClient.settings_to_cmd_args_env initializes env = None and only sets it to a dict when a password is present, correctly signaling 'no env overrides' via None.", "score": 1.325767, "tokens": 43, "rank": 9, "timestamp": 1782458477.665685}]}}
